# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
debug
target

# wasm-pack output
/pkg

# macOS
.DS_Store

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# Generated by cargo mutants
# Contains mutation testing data
**/mutants.out*/

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/

# Compiled C++ converter binary (rebuild via the command in scripts/README.md)
scripts/vdb_to_qvg

# Local Python venvs
.venv/
**/.venv/

# Third-party VDB-derived grids + renders. The Quasi crate is Apache 2.0
# but the Disney Cloud Data Set is CC BY-SA 3.0, so anything derived from
# it has to live outside the repo or be explicitly relicensed (we don't).
# Render it locally per the scripts/README.md workflow; the procedurally-
# baked `cumulus_64.qvg` IS committed since it's ours.
data/grids/disney_*.qvg
data/grids/wdas_*.qvg
data/output/cornell_disney_*.png

# Reference render EXRs. Generated from `.gltf` + the renderer at HEAD
# (see `data/output/README.md`). Keeping them in git was costing ~190 MB
# of clone weight that almost no consumer reads — the PNGs carry the
# visual gallery story, and RMSE-against-EXR analyses prefer freshly
# rendered ground truth over committed bytes. Re-render locally with
# `cargo run -- render --scene <gltf> ...` when needed.
data/output/*.exr

# Plan 0022 PT-sponza-baseline: Sponza glTF asset (~53 MB across 71
# files) lives on contributor disk only. Re-fetch with
# `python3 scripts/fetch_sponza.py`. Source + licence:
# https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF-Sample-Models 2.0/Sponza.
data/gltf/sponza/

# Plan 0024 PT-chess-showcase + future PT-* scene-delivery plans:
# Khronos sample-assets distributions (ABeautifulGame ~30 MB, etc.)
# live on contributor disk only. Re-fetch with
# `python3 scripts/fetch_khronos_scene.py <ModelName>`. Source +
# licence: https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF-Sample-Assets.
data/gltf/abeautifulgame/
